column5: Andrew (Pooch) was good enough to take me out on his boat yesterday. We trolled from about 10:30am til 5pm. The fish got to see a pretty good selection of lures. When it was time to call it quits I was reeling the lure in after unclipping the board and this walleye hit feet from the boat. 24.5 x 15. not a bad first BOQ walleye. The weather was great and it was good to be on the water

thanks for the report & nice walleye pic.....well after this big weather event rolls through in the next few days there wont be anybody on the bay for at least 3-4 days its gonna get real nasty...  well we gotta expect it this time of year especially down around the quinte area
fishing this time of year without freezing can't beat it
A very respectable walleye in any waters.  I love fall fishing.
That's was as close to getting skunked as I've ever been. Count it as the lucky fish. Guess we should have been casting!
Glad you guys got out, and nice way to end, with a nice fish while getting ready to call it a day...  Mike
Congrats on your fisrst BOQ walleye!!!!!!!!!
Nice job out there!  I went on my first trip to BOQ with fishindevil...had a blast!  Great looking eye you got there!!
